Peter Ndegwa named Safaricom CEO             Japheth Ogila  24th Oct 2019 16:38:16 GMT +0300 Japheth Ogila  24th Oct 2019 16:38:16 GMT +0300 Japheth Ogila   Diageo's Peter Ndegwa who will take over as Safaricom CEO from April 1, 2020.  Diageo's Peter Ndegwa who will take over as Safaricom CEO from April 1, 2020. Diageo's Peter Ndegwa who will take over as Safaricom CEO from April 1, 2020. The Safaricom board has resolved to appoint Peter Ndegwa as the company’s Chief Executive Officer effective April 1, 2020. A statement from the board says Mr Ndegwa joins the telco from Diageo PLC where he is the Managing Director of Diageo Continental Europe. According to the statement, “Peter oversees the operations of Diageo PLC in 50 countries in Western and Eastern Europe, Russia, Middle East and North Africa region. He had previously served for seven years as CEO in Guinness Nigeria PLC and Guinness Ghana Breweries PLC, where he transformed the two operations to deliver a double- digit growth by investing in people, introducing new brands and reorganising the businesses.” Prior to that, adds the board, “Peter served for eight years across a range of senior Executive Director roles at EABL (a Diageo subsidiary) based in Nairobi. Serving as the Group Chief Finance Officer (CFO), Group Strategy Director, Sales Director, and as an Executive Director on the EABL Board, he was part of the team that saw the EABL business more than doubled in value – and winning the coveted Most Respected Business Award in East Africa for five years in a row.”      SEE ALSO :Safaricom employee charged with Sh45,600 theft SEE ALSO : Safaricom employee charged with Sh45,600 theft    For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   SEE ALSO :Safaricom gives economy Sh600b boost in a year SEE ALSO : Safaricom gives economy Sh600b boost in a year Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standar